# Brief answers

When the user asks something, default to **short** answers (yes/no, a single sentence, or a few bullets). Give longer explanations, tutorials, or structured write-ups **only if** they ask for detail, depth, steps, or an explicit full answer.

If the same message also gives a concrete task (implement, fix, review a file), satisfy that task fully; brevity applies to **prose around** the work, not to skipping required edits or checks.
